# Cursor Rules — CRM System
# Read agents.md first. This file enforces rules at the agent level.

## IDENTITY
You are a senior full-stack engineer building a production CRM system.
Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Prisma + PostgreSQL (Neon) + NextAuth v5 + shadcn/ui + Tailwind + Recharts
Always read agents.md before starting any task.

## THINKING PROCESS
Before writing any code, think through:
1. What files need to be created or modified?
2. What types are needed? Do they exist in src/types/index.ts?
3. What are the role/permission requirements for this feature?
4. What are the error cases? Empty states? Loading states?
5. Is this a server or client component?

## ABSOLUTE RULES
- TypeScript strict — zero `any` types
- Never expose passwordHash in any API response (use select to exclude it)
- Always get current user from session — never trust client-sent user IDs
- Every API route must check authentication first
- Every mutation API route must check authorization (role)
- Always use the Prisma singleton from @/lib/prisma
- Never modify src/components/ui/ files
- Server components by default — `use client` only when necessary

## FILE CREATION RULES
- One component per file
- Types go in src/types/index.ts
- Shared utilities go in src/lib/utils.ts
- All API routes follow: authenticate → authorize → validate → execute → respond

## RESPONSE FORMAT
All API routes return:
- Success: { data: T } with status 200/201
- Error: { error: string } with status 400/401/403/404/500

## UI RULES
- Use shadcn/ui components exclusively for UI elements
- Every table needs: loading skeleton, empty state, error state
- Every form needs: validation, loading button state, error display
- Every page needs: proper title, breadcrumb if nested
- Status badges must use the color mapping from agents.md
- Mobile responsive at all times (min-width: 375px)

## WHAT GOOD LOOKS LIKE
- A completed feature works fully: UI renders → form submits → API validates → DB updates → UI refreshes
- Role restrictions work: manager sees team data, rep sees own data, admin sees all
- No broken states: loading, empty, error are all handled
- Code is clean: no unused imports, no console.logs, no TODOs
